def fibonacci(n: int) -> list[int]:
    """Return a list of the first n Fibonacci numbers."""
    if n <= 0:
        return []
    if n == 1:
        return [0]

    fibs = [0, 1]
    while len(fibs) < n:
        next_val = fibs[-1] + fibs[-2]
        fibs.append(next_val)
    return fibs

How it works:
The function initializes the first two Fibonacci numbers in a list and then repeatedly appends the sum of the last two elements until it has n elements, handling small n as special cases.
